newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soy products close lower as soybeans slide.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soy products close lower as soybeans slide.

text.p: CBOT soy product futures closed lower on heavier-than-expected rainfall over the weekend in key U.S. soybean growing states, traders said.
Soyoil also remained under pressure from persistent heavy deliveries on the September contracts while soymeal again was underpinned by the posting of no deliveries on the September, they said.
Recent commercial bull spreading in soymeal and news China bought at least 50,000 tonnes of U.S. soymeal also underpinned soymeal futures, the traders said.
But "very quiet and very slow ahead of the report," a trader said.
USDA at 0730 CDT Wednesday will release its September crop production report.
Soymeal futures volume was estimated at 15,000 contracts, down from 21,210 Friday, according to the CBOT. Soymeal options volume was estimated at 1,700 contracts, down from 2,929 contracts Friday.
Soyoil futures closed 0.10 to 0.40 cent per lb lower, with September down 0.10 at 25.40 cents. Soymeal was $1.70 per ton lower to $0.50 higher, with September down $0.90 at $266.80.
Soyoil futures volume was estimated at 15,000 contracts, down from 19,387 Friday. Soyoil options volume was estimated at 800 contracts, down from 1,438 Friday.
